Date:   Tue May 13 13:16:18 2025 +0100

    HADOOP-19554. LocalDirAllocator still doesn't always recover from directory deletion (#7683)
    
    
    The LocalDIrManager class used to allocate disk space for HDFS block storage
    and cloud connector buffers should  now recover from directory deletion on
    all codepaths.
    This situation can occur in cloud connectors uses when cron jobs
    clean up temp directories on a schedule.
    
    There is also significantly better logging of the allocation process failures.
    
    Contributed by Steve Loughran

